22 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-150.1 of Title 70, unless
24 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
Req. No. 10248 Page 1

1 A. The State Board of Education shall develop an Academic
2 Performance Index (API) to be used to measure performance of
3 schools, including the academic performance of students. The index
4 shall consist of a variety of indicators including, but not limited
5 to:
6 1. Attendance rates;
7 2. Dropout rates;
8 3. Results of the Oklahoma School Testing Program administered
9 pursuant to Section 1210.508 of this title;
10 4. Advanced Placement participation;
11 5. Graduation rates for secondary school students;
12 6. Scores of nationally norm-referenced college entrance exams;
13 and
14 7. College remediation rates.
15 B. The data collected for the API shall be disaggregated, when
16 available, by socioeconomic status and ethnic group. Oklahoma
17 School Testing Program results shall constitute no less than sixty
18 percent (60%) of the value of the index.
19 C. The State Board of Education shall adopt expected annual
20 percentage growth targets for the state level, school districts, and
21 all school sites based on their API baseline score. The minimum
22 percentage growth target shall be five percent (5%) annually.
23 However, the State Board of Education may set differential growth
24 targets based on grade level of instruction.
Req. No. 10248 Page 2

1 D. The academic performance of students who are enrolled full-
2 time in an online program that is offered by a school district or
3 charter school that is not the district of residence or is not
4 located in the district of residence of the student shall be
5 reported separately by the school district or charter school, and
6 shall not be included when determining the Academic Performance
7 Index of the school district or charter school.
